  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Educate hearing-impaired children in Timbuktu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;Ecole des deficients auditifs&quot; is an initiation of the association of parents of deaf children in Timbuktu. It was established in 2007 with support from the Norwegian Stromme Foundation and the French Embassy in Mali, allowing us to hire two trained teachers and management, and construct three classrooms and latrines. Today, there are 30 children enrolled at the school and three teachers. This school is the first of its kind in the region and is greatly welcomed by the Ministry of Education.</narrative>
  </description>
